# Button Component Patterns

## Prefer `buttonVariants()` over `Button asChild`

When styling links or anchor elements as buttons, use `buttonVariants()` directly instead of wrapping with `Button` and `asChild`.

**Preferred:**

```tsx
<Link className={buttonVariants()} href="/path">Text</Link>
<a className={buttonVariants({ variant: 'ghost', size: 'sm' })} href="/path">Text</a>
```

**Avoid:**

```tsx
<Button asChild><Link href="/path">Text</Link></Button>
<Button asChild><a href="/path">Text</a></Button>
```

This pattern avoids React child validation errors and simplifies the component tree.
